## What to do right now (before starting Phase 4):

  1. Run the manual Phase 3 checklist end-to-end (country auto-select, winter behavior, satellite/seasonal tiles, proxy cache HIT/
     MISS).
  2. Run full go test ./internal/tiles/... in your local environment with Redis/network enabled (sandbox here can’t validate socket-
     based tests).
  3. Add one lightweight e2e smoke test for map behavior (topo auto-select + season toggle + sentinel request).
  4. Decide if the current in-memory tile rate limiter is enough for your deployment shape (single instance is fine; multi-instance
     should move to shared limiting).

  What to keep in mind soon:

  1. Web bundle size is large (MapPage chunk ~1.7MB); plan code-splitting before phases add more UI/features.
  2. Add tile-proxy observability (cache hit ratio, upstream error rate, per-provider request volume).

  No blocking issues from my latest review.